>
	<p>
		<strong>FloodBoy: IoT-Powered Blockchain</strong> is an innovative IoT-powered flood monitoring system designed to provide 
		real-time water level data and early warning alerts to communities at risk of flooding. By combining 
		cutting-edge sensor technology with blockchain transparency, FloodBoy: IoT-Powered Blockchain aims to create a more resilient 
		and informed society.
	</p>

	<h2>Beta Version Notice</h2>
	<p>
		<em>This application is currently in <strong>BETA</strong> and is intended for research purposes only.</em> 
		We are actively developing and testing features to ensure reliability and accuracy before full deployment. 
		Data displayed may be from simulated sensors or test environments. Please do not rely on this system 
		for critical flood monitoring or emergency decisions at this time.
	</p>

	<h2>Our Mission</h2>
	<p>
		Flooding affects millions of people worldwide each year, causing devastating losses to life and property. 
		FloodBoy: IoT-Powered Blockchain seeks to democratize access to flood monitoring technology by creating an open, transparent, 
		and community-driven platform that empowers local communities to better prepare for and respond to 
		flood events.
	</p>

	<h2>Technology Stack</h2>
	<p>
		Our system leverages modern web technologies and blockchain infrastructure:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>IoT Sensors:</strong> Ultra-low power water level sensors with LoRaWAN connectivity</li>
		<li><strong>Blockchain:</strong> Immutable data storage on JIBCHAIN for transparency and trust</li>
		<li><strong>Real-time Updates:</strong> MQTT protocol for instant data transmission</li>
		<li><strong>Web Interface:</strong> Built with Astro for optimal performance and accessibility</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Research and Development</h2>
	<p>
		As a research project, FloodBoy: IoT-Powered Blockchain is exploring innovative approaches to:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Incentivized sensor deployment through blockchain rewards</li>
		<li>Community-validated flood event reporting</li>
		<li>Machine learning for flood prediction and pattern analysis</li>
		<li>Integration with existing emergency response systems</li>
	</ul>

